@MariaSolOs, thanks for working on this! I was also hit by #25375 some times ago so wanted to chime in and share som thoughts.

Although this does a great job of displaying caught errors, it doesn't show any stacktrace. A fix I had internally and locally (but haven't wrapped up enough yet to submit a PR) makes use of `xpcall` and `vim.notify` to print the full stacktrace (which is more aggressive but arguably more useful). I'm curious what would be more preferred way -- regarding how much verbosity we'd want to have.

I suggest we could use a similar approach -- I could also help work on this sometime soon.
